A simple plugin that adds a custom button to the tinyMCE editor to simplify in-line expert peer review for academic blogging.

== Description ==
In-line Expert Peer Review Plugin is a simple WordPress plugin providing that adds in-line EPR functionality to the tinyMCE editor.
This plugin creates a custom <span> class which uses data attributes to display expert peer review commentary as a CSS tooltip.


= Features =
* Insert stylized in-line tooltips for expert peer review with a single click, without the use of shortcodes.

= Planned Features =
* Ability to easily edit or delete in-line commentary from the visual editor
* Ability to customize tooltip appearance from plugin page


= Contributing =
If you're a developer and would like to contribute, you can do so via this plugin's [GitHub Repository](https://github.com/skobner/inline_plugin.git).

== Installation ==

1. Upload the `inline_plugin` folder to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory.
2. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress.
